@startuml Seq_Notifications
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 1.5
skinparam sequenceGroupBorderColor #2980B9
skinparam noteBorderColor #F39C12
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #FEF9E7

title HumatiQ — Notification System Flow

actor User
participant "React Frontend" as FE
participant "FastAPI Backend" as BE
participant "NotificationService" as NS
database "MongoDB\n(notifications)" as Mongo
participant "SMTP / Email" as Mail

== Creating a Notification (Internal Trigger) ==
note over BE
  Triggered by various events:
  - Application submitted
  - Quiz assigned
  - Interview scheduled
  - Status changed
  - Deadline approaching
  - Reminder due
end note

BE -> NS : create(\n  user_id, type, category,\n  title, message, link, metadata\n)
NS -> Mongo : insert notifications\n{ user_id, type, category,\n  title, message, link,\n  is_read: false, created_at: now }
Mongo --> NS : notification_id

NS -> NS : Build HTML email template
NS -> Mail : Send via SMTP\n{ to: user_email, subject, body }
Mail --> NS : sent

NS --> BE : Notification created

== Polling Unread Count (Frontend) ==
note right of FE
  Frontend polls every 30s
  to show bell badge count
end note
FE -> BE : GET /api/notifications/unread-count\n[Authorization: Bearer JWT]
BE -> BE : Extract user_id from JWT
BE -> Mongo : count({ user_id, is_read: false })
Mongo --> BE : { count: 3 }
BE --> FE : { unread_count: 3 }
FE -> FE : Update notification bell badge

== Fetching Notifications ==
User -> FE : Click notification bell
FE -> BE : GET /api/notifications\n?limit=20&skip=0
BE -> Mongo : find({ user_id })\n.sort({ created_at: -1 })
Mongo --> BE : notifications[]
BE --> FE : List of notifications
FE -> User : Display notification dropdown

== Mark Single Notification as Read ==
User -> FE : Click on a notification
FE -> BE : PATCH /api/notifications/{id}/read
BE -> Mongo : update { is_read: true }
Mongo --> BE : updated
BE --> FE : 200 OK
FE -> FE : Remove unread indicator
FE -> FE : Navigate to notification.link

== Mark All as Read ==
User -> FE : Click "Mark all as read"
FE -> BE : PATCH /api/notifications/read-all
BE -> Mongo : updateMany({ user_id },\n  { is_read: true })
Mongo --> BE : updated count
BE --> FE : 200 OK
FE -> FE : Clear all unread indicators
FE -> FE : Update badge to 0

== Delete Notification ==
User -> FE : Dismiss a notification
FE -> BE : DELETE /api/notifications/{id}
BE -> Mongo : deleteOne({ _id, user_id })
Mongo --> BE : deleted
BE --> FE : 204 No Content
FE -> FE : Remove from list

== Notification Categories & Types ==
note over Mongo
  Categories:
  ├── application
  │   ├── "New application received" (HR)
  │   ├── "Application shortlisted" (Candidate)
  │   └── "Application rejected" (Candidate)
  ├── quiz
  │   ├── "Quiz assigned" (Candidate)
  │   └── "Quiz submitted" (HR)
  ├── interview
  │   ├── "Slots proposed" (Candidate)
  │   ├── "Interview confirmed" (Both)
  │   ├── "Reminder: 24h" (Both)
  │   └── "Reminder: 1h" (Both)
  └── system
      ├── "Pipeline completed" (HR)
      └── "Login detected" (User)

  Types: info | success | warning | error
end note

@enduml
